# ========================================
# Claude-like AI Chatbot Configuration
# ========================================
# Multiple AI providers for intelligent responses to any question
# Choose one or more providers (will fallback automatically)

# OpenAI Configuration (Most Intelligent - Recommended)
# Get your API key from: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
REACT_APP_OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-your-openai-api-key-here

# HuggingFace Configuration (Good Alternative - Free Tier Available)
# Get your API key from: https://huggingface.co/settings/tokens
REACT_APP_HUGGINGFACE_API_KEY=hf_your-huggingface-token-here

# Groq Configuration (Fast and Free)
# Get your Groq API key from: https://console.groq.com/keys
REACT_APP_GROQ_API_KEY=gsk_your-actual-groq-api-key-here

# Firebase Configuration (keep your existing values)
# REACT_APP_FIREBASE_API_KEY=your-firebase-key
# REACT_APP_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=your-project.firebaseapp.com
# REACT_APP_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your-project-id
# REACT_APP_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=your-project.appspot.com
# REACT_APP_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=123456789
# REACT_APP_FIREBASE_APP_ID=1:123456789:web:abcdef123456

# ========================================
# How to Use:
# ========================================
# 1. Choose your preferred AI provider:
#    - OpenAI: Most intelligent, requires paid account
#    - HuggingFace: Good quality, has free tier
#    - Groq: Fast and free
# 2. Get API key from the provider's website
# 3. Copy this file to ".env.local"
# 4. Add your API key(s) to the appropriate variable(s)
# 5. Keep the REACT_APP_ prefix (React requirement)
# 6. Restart your development server: npm start
# 7. The chatbot will automatically use the best available provider
#
# Note: If no API keys are provided, it will use enhanced local responses
# ========================================

# Testing Tips:
# - Test with questions like "Explain quantum physics" or "What is the meaning of life?"
# - Check browser DevTools Console for any error messages
# - The chatbot should handle any topic intelligently
# - If one provider fails, it automatically tries the next one